 For Fly Machine principals, Token Policy can match immutable `org_id` and `app_id`, readable `org_name` and `app_name`, or both. Immutable IDs are the recommended policy key. Name-only Fly rules are supported only as an explicit compatibility mode because Fly names are easier to rename or reuse than IDs. Optional machine-level narrowing follows the selected identity mode: ID rules narrow by `machine_id`, name rules narrow by `machine_name`, and ID-and-name rules narrow by both.
+
+Fly Machine principal derivation requires these verified token claims: `sub`, `org_id`, `org_name`, `app_id`, `app_name`, `machine_id`, `machine_name`, and `machine_version`. The `sub` claim must exactly equal `org_name:app_name:machine_name`. cyspbot also accepts optional Fly runtime claims `region`, `image`, `image_digest`, and `image_tag` for policy logging and future rule data.
